<strong>Open a terminal and change directories into /tmp</strong>
<strong>Open a browser and navigate to http://packages.ubuntu.com/RELEASE/all/vrms/download and select a mirror, then download the .deb file into /tmp</strong>
<strong>If you manually installed vrms in the past, uninstall it.</strong>

<strong>This will make sure that the graphical GDebi interface works properly.</strong>
<dl>
    <!-- UNVERIFIED STEPS -->
    <dt>Open /tmp in File Manager</dt>
    <dt>Right-click the downloaded .deb file and select GDebi Package Installer</dt>
        <dd>vrms should open in GDebi and the "Description" tag should be active with a description of vrms</dd>
    <dt>Click the "Install Package" button</dt>
        <dd>You should be prompted for your password</dd>
    <dt>Enter your password and press Enter</dt>
        <dd>After a short amount of time, a dialog box should appear saying, "Installation Finished"</dd>
    <dt>Click the "Close" button on the dialog box</dt>
        <dd>The original dialog box should appear with three (3) buttons instead of two (2)</dd>
    <dt>Select the "Details" tab</dt>
        <dd>The package details should properly show</dd>
    <dt>Select the "Included files" tab</dt>
        <dd>A list of files should properly show with several dropdown menus</dd>
    <dt>Click the "Remove Package" button</dt>
        <dd>After a short amount of time, a dialog box should appear saying, "Removal finished"</dd>
    <dt>Click the "Close" button on the dialog box</dt>
        <dd>The original dialog box should appear with two (2) buttons</dd>
    <dt>Install the package again and close the additional dialog box</dt>
        <dd>The original dialog box should appear with three (3) buttons instead of two (2)</dd>
    <dt>Click the "Reinstall Package" button</dt>
        <dd>After a short amount of time, a dialog box should appear saying, "Installation Finished"</dd>
    <dt>Install the package again and close the additional dialog box</dt>
        <dd>The original dialog box should appear with three (3) buttons</dd>
    <dt>Open a terminal, type "vrms", and press Return</dt>
        <dd>vrms should function like normal, showing the nonfree packages on your system</dd>
</dl>
<strong>This will make sure that the command line GDebi interface works properly.</strong>
<dl>
    <!-- STEP AS EXPECTED RESULT: "type y then return" -->
    <dt>Run the following command in your terminal to remove vrms: sudo apt purge vrms</dt>
        <dd>Apt should prompt you to remove vrms, type "y" then Return, then apt should successfully remove vrms</dd>
    <!-- UNVERIFIED STEPS -->
    <dt>Change directories into /tmp</dt>
    <dt>Run the following command to install vrms: sudo -H gdebi vrms_PACKAGEVERSION_all.deb</dt>
        <dd>GDebi should prompt you to install vrms, type "y" then Return, then GDebi should successfully install vrms</dd>
    <dt>Run the following command to check the version of GDebi: gdebi --version</dt>
        <dd>This should output the version of GDebi</dd>
</dl>
<strong>
    If all actions produce the expected results listed, please <a href="results#add_result">submit</a> a 'passed' result.
    If an action fails, or produces an unexpected result, please <a href="results#add_result">submit</a> a 'failed' result and <a href="../../buginstructions">file a bug</a>.
    Please be sure to include the bug number when you <a href="results#add_result">submit</a> your result.
</strong>
